candidates.title: Update time requirement from 0.1 to 0.2

labels.name: dependencies
labels.description: Pull requests that update a dependency file

candidates.body:
Updates the requirements on [time](https://github.com/time-rs/time) to permit the latest version.
Release notes

Sourced from time's releases.

v0.2.0

See #190 for major details. This is essentially a new crate compared to v0.1, and only has a few methods for back-compatibility where trivially feasible.

Minimum supported Rust version: 1.40.0

Commits
  • ab09c47 Provide details when displaying component errors
  • 7528763 All internals should have be named "unchecked"
  • 17c1a2e Update tests for non-panicking defaults
  • be01703 Reduce duplication, new hidden methods for macros
  • e19b951 Put panicking API behind feature flag
  • 6913768 Add ParseError to Error enum
  • e53ca14 Guaranteed stable serde representation
  • 3139629 Unified error type for simpler handling
  • 8359a07 Forward-compatible component range error type
  • 20b27cb Rename OutOfRangeError to ConversionRangeError
  • Additional commits viewable in compare view
